Class EximResourceConfigImpl

java.lang.Object
  com.smartitengineering.exim.impl.EximResourceConfigImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
EximResourceConfig
public class EximResourceConfigImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements EximResourceConfig

This implementation represents the configuration of a class. 2 configuration objects are considered to be equal if they represent the same class.

Since:
0.4
Author:
imyousuf

isAccessByPropertyEnabled

public boolean isAccessByPropertyEnabled()
Description copied from interface: EximResourceConfig
Setting for testing whether to access members by property accessors or field. If access is set by property and a setter is not available that it will be ignored.

Specified by:
isAccessByPropertyEnabled in interface EximResourceConfig
Returns:
True if access is to done by getter/setter and false if reflection is to be used for setting property value.

getAssociationConfigs

public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,AssociationConfig> getAssociationConfigs()
Description copied from interface: EximResourceConfig
Returns the configuration map for the associations of this resource object class. Since every type in Java extends Object we consider every member in a resource class to be an association and thus store its configuration in thus manner. Name of the property is the key to the map.

Specified by:
getAssociationConfigs in interface EximResourceConfig
Returns:
A property name keyed configuration map of all the associations

getPriority

public int getPriority()
Description copied from interface: EximResourceConfig
Represents the priority of the resource domain. It is applicable only for interfaces. If a non resource domain concrete object implements more than one resource domain annotated interfaces, then based on descending order the priority will popped from a priority queue.

Specified by:
getPriority in interface EximResourceConfig
Returns:
Priority of this resource domain, 0 by default.

isExportBasicTypesInTypeElementEnabled

public boolean isExportBasicTypesInTypeElementEnabled()
Description copied from interface: EximResourceConfig
Returns whether basic return types such as String, Integer, Long should encapsulated in their distinct XML elements or simply as text content. The reason for this to be true could be for better readability of the XML.

Specified by:
isExportBasicTypesInTypeElementEnabled in interface EximResourceConfig
Returns:
True if and only if the basic types are to be encapsulated in their respective element as defined in schema http://www.smartitengineering.com/smart-dao/exim/basic-types
